<paragraph blockId="3.[113,1089,699,819]" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">
Only the male from Malšice (
<collectingCountry box="[459,632,699,723]" name="Czech Republic" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">Czech Republic</collectingCountry>
) corresponds to the Becker’s redescription and differs from all species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Becker" authorityYear="1894" box="[532,673,732,755]" class="Insecta" family="Scathophagidae" genus="Amaurosoma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[532,673,732,755]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">Amaurosoma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the following characters: first aristomere long, praegonite broadened apically, and the shape of abdominal sternites 3-5 including lobes. I regard this species as valid.
</paragraph>
